  "query": "so I'm looking at @product/research/ass-032/SCOPE.md This scope got a couple things not quite rigth.  Unimatrix is intended to be a general knowledge management system, that is workflow aware in its nature.  Its default (and current repository) is configured for software development, but other domain packs may include different categories, and different phase descriptions.  Common though, is that there will be categories defined, and there will be phases defined for the workflow.  \\\n\\\nOur goal is to make Unimatrix a self-learning knowledge engine.  This doesn't HAVE to be based on where we've come from.. my goal is to achieve the objective.  However, it behooves us to FULLY understand our current capabilities, the search tools we have, the paths that we have, and the current selection pipeline that we have...  But also to figure out how to achieve our goal... this is a research only effort.  Update the scope, thn launch a multifaceted research, search for novel concepts like github/ruvnet/ruvector or other papers/research.  We're in rust, so adding neural models is possible... what are our options is what we need to understand.",
